Context:
The current description display at line 104-105:
```typescript
const desc = tool.description || '';
console.log(`    ${pc.cyan(tool.name)}${padding}  ${pc.dim(desc)}`);
```
For browser tools, descriptions are long multi-sentence strings starting with '[Disabled]' or '[Requires approval]' followed by long descriptions including security advisories.

Changes:
Add a truncation helper and use it:
```typescript
const truncateDesc = (desc: string, maxLen = 100): string => {
  if (!desc) return '';
  // Find first sentence end
  const sentenceEnd = desc.search(/\.(?:\s|$)/);
  const cutoff = sentenceEnd !== -1 && sentenceEnd + 1 < maxLen ? sentenceEnd + 1 : maxLen;
  if (desc.length <= cutoff) return desc;
  return `${desc.slice(0, cutoff).trimEnd()}...`;
};
// In the loop:
const desc = truncateDesc(tool.description || '');
console.log(`    ${pc.cyan(tool.name)}${padding}  ${pc.dim(desc)}`);
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the `--json` output path (line 70: `console.log(JSON.stringify(tools, null, 2))`)
- Do NOT change handleToolSchema — it still shows the full description
- The truncation should preserve the '[Disabled]' or '[Requires approval]' prefix that the server adds to descriptions
